                      MONSTER ALIGNMENT GUIDELINES
                      ============================


Introduction:
------------

This purpose of this document is to present suggested guidelines for
the alignments assigned to monsters.  These guidelines contain 
recommended values and definitions of each alignment.  These guidelines
are designed to help prevent the alignment problem experienced during
the first half of 1996 and to ensure that all wizards are on the same
alignment scale.  The administration of Darkwind suggests these
ranges of values for monsters.  Extreme alignment values are not
forbidden, just discouraged due to their effects on players and their
respective guild abilities.


Alignment Definitions:
----------------------

Saintly            - Saintly creatures value nothing more than the
                     pursuit of beauty, kindness, freedom, and truth.
                     In order for this pursuit to succeed, all that is
                     not good must be eliminated.

Good               - Good creatures strongly believe in beauty, kindness,
                     truth, and freedom.  However in their pursuits
                     for truth sometimes certain sacrifices may have
                     to be made in the name of all that is good.

Nice               - Nice creatures are those that believe in things
                     such as beauty, kindness, truth, and freedom
                     as they will ultimately make the world a better
                     place by bringing maximum benefits to all.

Neutral            - Neutral creatures look upon all the other
                     alignments as being part of the natural order
                     of things.  They think that the alignments
                     must exist in order for the natural balance of
                     of things to hold.  Neutral alignment also applies
                     to most natural animals and other creatures that
                     do not care about and have no concept of good and
                     evil.

Nasty              - Nasty creatures can be those that have just
                     entered a lifestyle of evil pursuits.  They
                     are lacking respect for one or more of the
                     following: life, beauty, truth, freedom.
                     They may have also entered into this lifestyle
                     unwittingly, but only value themselves and as
                     much power they can get.

Evil               - Creatures of this alignment hold things such as
                     life, beauty, truth, freedom, with little value
                     and generally scorn them.  These creatures
                     are generally out to gain power and control over
                     others through fear, torture, and any other means
                     necessary.  Typical creatures in this range include
                     fiends, devils, lesser warlords, some dragons,
                     and demons.

Demonic            - Creatures of this alignment have total disdain
                     and scorn for life, beauty, truth, and freedom.
                     Their only purpose is total conquest
                     of the world through any means necessary, most
                     likely at the expense of others.  They also
                     believe in the total eradication of good
                     creatures and often capture and manipulate them
                     into being their slaves.  It is extremely
                     rare for a normal creature to become this evil
                     without some supernatural or magical assistance.
                     These creatures are generally very powerful demon
                     lords, lords or dukes of other plains of existance,
                     or manifestations brought into the physical world
                     by evil forces.

Ethics definitions:
-------------------

Lawful              - Creatures of lawful alignment are extremely
                      disciplined and live according to rigorous codes
                      of behavior.  They tend to have highly regimented
                      social structures, and will follow their superiors
                      with extreme obedience (and expect the same from
                      their inferiors).  Examples might be a legendary
                      knight, a stereotypical samurai warrior, or a
                      clan of dark elf warriors.  (Note that it is
                      possible to be lawful and evil; in this case, the
                      code of behavior that the creature follows is
                      itself evil.)

Orderly             - Orderly creatures are those who try to live their
                      lives according to a code.  They tend to be very
                      disciplined and methodical, but suffer the
                      occasional lapse.  Orderly creatures often live in
                      a regimented society, where they generally defer
                      to those of greater rank and expect respect from
                      those of lesser rank.  Examples would include most
                      knights, orcish war-bands, or dark elf commoners.

Just                - Just creatures are those who believe in a code of
                      behavior and generally try to live according to
                      that code, but who are willing to make "reasonable"
                      exceptions.  These creatures believe that the code
                      is a good idea in theory, and necessary for the
                      protection of society, but they overlook smaller
                      details in practice.  They tend to be fairly
                      disciplined and organized, but not notably so.

Neutral             - Creatures with neutral ethics don't particularly
                      care about ethics and codes of honor, or they don't
                      follow any particular code.  This includes most
                      natural animals and other creatures who cannot
                      understand the concept of ethics, as well as those
                      who are simply not concerned by the matter.

Lawless             - Lawless creatures have no use for the ethical codes
                      society imposes.  Though they do not go out of
                      their way to break laws, they will if they feel
                      they must, in order to attain their goals.  Lawless
                      ethics can also indicate someone who is an
                      individualist and who sees no need for outwardly-
                      imposed rules of behavior.  In this way, a lawless
                      creature can still be a good individual, just as a
                      lawful creature can be evil in nature.

Entropic            - Entropic creatures do not recognize outwardly-imposed
                      rules of behavior.  They tend to be disorganized by
                      others' standards, and are seen as too undisciplined
                      to work in large groups, since they do not follow
                      orders well, nor do they acknowledge any permanent
                      leader or ruler.  Examples of entropic creatures
                      would include pirates, trolls, and some lesser demons.

Chaotic             - Chaotic creatures are actively opposed to codes of
                      behavior.  They will break laws with abandon, holding
                      only their own judgment important.  They will never
                      acknowledge another as ruler willingly, and have
                      difficulty even joining forces with other creatures
                      temporarily.  They are extreme individualists.
                      Examples would include some ancient dragons, chaos
                      demon lords, the most infamous pirates, etc.


Alignments:                         Suggested Range:

-----------                         ----------------


Saintly                               1000 - above
Good                                   500 - 999
Nice                                   300 - 499
Neutral                               -299 - 299
Nasty                                 -499 - -300
Evil                                  -999 - -500
Demonic                              -1000 - below

Ethics:                              Suggested Range:
---------                           ---------------


Lawful                                1000 - above
Orderly                                500 - 999
Just                                   300 - 499
Neutral                               -299 - 299
Lawless                               -499 - -300
Entropic                             -999 - -500
Chaotic                              -1000 - below

Misc.
-----

It should be noted that extreme alignment values (above 2000 or
below -2000), although not forbidden, should be rare and used with
caution.  Creatures with these alignments should be legendary on
Darkwind as it should be almost all but impossible for mere mortal
creatures to have such alignments.  However, unworldly creatures from
other planes of existence that defy the laws of nature can be known
to have such alignments.


Conclusions:
------------

The purpose of this doc is not to target any one person or group
of people in particular, it is to provide suggested guidelines
for the assignment of alignments to monsters. This doc can be revised
at any time.  Such revision will follow with posts to the wizboards.
If you are unsure about anything in this document, please post to
the document wiz board. In addition, please provide a variety of
alignments in your area as it is unlikely that two creatures would
have the exact same alignment.  Extreme alignment values are also
discouraged because they can have adverse effects on players and
their respective guild abilities.

Note that everything in this document that applies to alignment
applies equally to ethics.

